theorem Topology.clopen_of_boundary_eq_empty
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure A \ interior A = (∅ : Set X) → IsOpen A ∧ IsClosed A := by
  intro hBoundary
  -- First, show `closure A ⊆ interior A`.
  have hClosSubInt : (closure A : Set X) ⊆ interior A := by
    intro x hxClos
    by_cases hxInt : x ∈ interior A
    · exact hxInt
    ·
      have hx : x ∈ closure A \ interior A := And.intro hxClos hxInt
      have : x ∈ (∅ : Set X) := by
        simpa [hBoundary] using hx
      exact False.elim (Set.not_mem_empty _ this)
  -- Hence `interior A = closure A`.
  have hIntEqClos : interior A = closure A := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · exact Topology.interior_subset_closure (A := A)
    · exact hClosSubInt
  -- Next, prove `interior A = A`.
  have hIntEqA : interior A = (A : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · exact interior_subset
    ·
      intro x hxA
      have hxClos : x ∈ closure A := subset_closure hxA
      exact hClosSubInt hxClos
  -- `A` is open since it equals its interior.
  have hOpen : IsOpen A := by
    have : IsOpen (interior A) := isOpen_interior
    simpa [hIntEqA] using this
  -- `A` is closed since it equals its closure.
  have hClosed : IsClosed A := by
    have hClosedClos : IsClosed (closure A) := isClosed_closure
    simpa [hIntEqClos] using hClosedClos
  exact And.intro hOpen hClosed

theorem Topology.interior_subset_interior_closure_union {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    interior A ⊆ interior (closure (A ∪ B)) := by
  intro x hx
  -- First, note that `A ⊆ closure (A ∪ B)`.
  have hSub : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A ∪ B) := by
    intro y hy
    -- `y ∈ A` implies `y ∈ A ∪ B`.
    have : (y : X) ∈ (A ∪ B : Set X) := Or.inl hy
    -- The universal property of the closure yields the claim.
    exact subset_closure this
  -- Monotonicity of `interior ∘ closure` gives the desired inclusion.
  exact (interior_mono hSub) hx
